Then $\mathbf{p}$ is the midpoint of $\mathbf{v}$ and $\mathbf{r},$ so
\[\mathbf{p} = \frac{\mathbf{v} + \mathbf{r}}{2}.\]We can solve for $\mathbf{r},$ to find $\mathbf{r} = 2 \mathbf{p} - \mathbf{v}.$  Then
